  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency health care services in new displacement areas in Borno state</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute towards one of the priorities of the health sector response namely &#x201C;To provide life-saving and life sustaining humanitarian health assistance to affected people&#x201D; by reducing morbidity and mortality among the displaced population through the provision of basic health services. Mobile health teams deployed to the affected areas will conduct four outreach sessions per week to treat common ailments, vaccinate children and screen children for malnutrition. WHO will ensure the mobile health teams have the necessary medical supplies to execute their duties. Quality of care will be monitored through regular supportive supervisions by WHO staff.</narrative>
  </description>
